value.value: Any substance in the body or expelled from the body that is in a gaseous state.
Any portion of gas located in a part of the respiratory system that is composed primarily of air.
The outgrowth of neuroectoderm located on the floor of the embryonic hypothalamus that gives rise to the neurohypophysis (posterior lobe) of the pituitary gland.
The area of axial mesoderm that develops into the prechordal plate.

The posterior parietal cortex is a portion of the parietal lobe which manipulates mental images, and integrates sensory and motor portions of the brain. Some sources say that it consists of Brodmann area 5 and Brodmann area 7. Other sources say it is only area 7.
Granular region of the insular cortex.
Agranular region of the insular cortex.
Endocardium that is part of the left atrium.
Parenchymal tissue that forms the pineal gland.
An multicellular anatomical structure that has subparts of multiple organs as a part.
A cluster of cells, largely surrounded by a morphological boundary.
Material anatomical entity consisting of multiple anatomical structures that are not connected to each other.
A collection of anatomical structures that are alike in terms of their morphology or developmental origin.
A region or zone on the surface of an organism that encompasses skin and any adnexa, down through muscles and bounded by underlying skeletal support structures.

A pathway of fibers originating in the lateral part of the entorhinal area, perforating the subiculum of the hippocampus, and running into the stratum moleculare of the hippocampus, where these fibers synapse with others that go to the dentate gyrus. (Dorland, 28th ed).
The epithelial layer covering the biliary system. This includes the epithelium of the gallbladder (when present) as well as the intrahepatic and extrahepatic bile ducts.
Any organ component layer that consists of smooth muscle tissue.
Any gaseous product of an excretory process.
Any excreted gas that is produced by the digestive tract.

definition.value: In mammals, mostly produced as a byproduct of bacterial fermentation in the gastrointestinal (GI) tract, especially the colon, and excreted through the rectum

value.value: Any portion of gas located in a part of the respiratory system.
Mesenchyme that is part of a developing jaw [Automatically generated definition].
A brain region defined by functional criteria, e.g. auditory cortex, rather than by structural or histological criteria.
